\fs24
\b WhatsApp Clone - Environment Variables and Database Setup\b0\par
\par
\b 1) Project Environment Variables\b0\par
\par
\b Backend (.env in backend folder)\b0\par
\par
\b MONGODB_URI\b0\par
Required: Yes\par
Example: mongodb://localhost:27017/whatsapp_clone\par
Description: MongoDB connection string used by Mongoose to connect to the database at backend startup.\par
Used in: backend/server.js\par
\par
\b PORT\b0\par
Required: Recommended\par
Example: 5000\par
Description: HTTP port used by the backend Express server. If missing, the app falls back to 5000.\par
Used in: backend/server.js\par
\par
\b JWT_SECRET\b0\par
Required: Recommended for secure deployments\par
Example: your_secret_key_here\par
Description: Secret key intended for JWT token signing/verification. Keep private and do not commit real values.\par
Used in: configured in backend environment template for authentication/security configuration.\par
\par
\b MESSAGE_RESTORE_WINDOW_MS\b0\par
Required: Optional\par
Example: 5000\par
Description: Time window (milliseconds) allowed to restore a deleted message. Server clamps this value to a safe range (1000 to 60000 ms).\par
Used in: backend/routes/messages.js\par
\par
\b Frontend (.env in frontend folder)\b0\par
\par
\b REACT_APP_API_URL\b0\par
Required: Yes for production deployments\par
Example: http://localhost:5000 (local), https://your-backend.onrender.com (hosted)\par
Description: Base URL used by frontend API calls and socket connection target.\par
Used in: frontend/src/config.js and frontend API/socket calls.\par
\par
\b 2) Database Setup Details\b0\par
\par
\b Database Engine\b0\par
MongoDB with Mongoose ODM\par
\par
\b Primary Collections\b0\par
\par
\b users\b0\par
Model: User\par
Key fields:\par
- username (String, required, unique)\par
- email (String, required, unique)\par
- password (String, required; stored as hashed value by registration flow)\par
- createdAt, updatedAt (timestamps enabled)\par
\par
\b messages\b0\par
Model: Message\par
Key fields:\par
- sender (ObjectId, ref User, required)\par
- receiver (ObjectId, ref User, required)\par
- content (String, required)\par
- status (sent | delivered | read)\par
- timestamp (Date)\par
- isDeleted (Boolean)\par
- deletedAt (Date or null)\par
\par
\b Local Database Setup\b0\par
\par
1. Install and run MongoDB locally.\par
2. Create backend/.env with at least:\par
   MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/whatsapp_clone\par
   PORT=5000\par
   JWT_SECRET=replace_with_secure_value\par
   MESSAGE_RESTORE_WINDOW_MS=5000\par
3. Start backend from project root or backend folder.\par
4. Backend connects to MongoDB automatically on startup.\par
\par
\b MongoDB Atlas Setup (Optional)\b0\par
\par
1. Create a MongoDB Atlas cluster.\par
2. Create a database user and allow network access from your app IPs.\par
3. Replace MONGODB_URI in backend/.env with Atlas URI format:\par
   mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@<cluster-url>/<db-name>?retryWrites=true&w=majority\par
4. Restart backend server.\par
\par
\b 3) Deployment Notes\b0\par
\par
- Backend deployment must define MONGODB_URI and JWT_SECRET as secure environment variables.\par
- Frontend deployment must define REACT_APP_API_URL pointing to deployed backend URL.\par
- Never commit real secrets into source control. Use .env files locally and platform env settings in production.\par
\par
\b Document generated from current project code and env templates.\b0\par
}
